# Refactor Plan: Split Monolithic index.html into ES Modules
#
# Goal: Break the single 4,615-line <script> block in index.html into
#        ~12 focused ES module files under js/, without losing any
#        functionality.  Tests are written and passing BEFORE each
#        refactoring step, so regressions are caught immediately.
#
# Run tests:
#   node tests.js              (unit tests — 184 tests, 978 assertions today)
#   npx playwright test        (e2e tests — browser-level gameplay)
#
# Current state (pre-refactor):
#   index.html  — 4,615 lines: HTML/CSS (~525) + inline <script type="module"> (~4,090)
#   tests.js    — 2,670 lines: 184 tests, re-implements pure logic from index.html
#   e2e/gameplay.spec.js — Playwright end-to-end tests
#   server.js   — Zero-dep static file server (already serves .js files)
#
# Strategy: "Tests First, Then Extract"
#   1. Expand unit tests to cover every system that will become its own file
#   2. Run all tests — confirm green
#   3. Extract each module one at a time, run all tests after each extraction
#   4. Update copilot-instructions.md to reflect new architecture

# ============================================================
# PHASE 0 — PREPARATION
# ============================================================

## 0.1  Baseline test run
- Run `node tests.js` — confirm 184 tests, 978 assertions, 0 failures
- Run `npx playwright test` — confirm all e2e tests pass
- Commit: "Green baseline before refactor"

## 0.2  Create js/ directory
- `mkdir js`
- No code changes yet

# ============================================================
# PHASE 1 — WRITE PRE-REFACTOR TESTS
# ============================================================
#
# For each module that will be extracted, add/verify test coverage in tests.js
# BEFORE moving any code.  This creates a safety net.
#
# Tests follow the project convention: pure-function re-implementations
# in tests.js, no DOM/Three.js, using the existing test()/assert() harness.
#
# After EVERY batch of new tests: run `node tests.js`, confirm green, commit.

## 1.1  Constants tests (target: js/constants.js)
- Already covered: DIRECTIONS, SIGNAL_STATES, RIGHT_TURN_DATA are used
  throughout existing tests
- Add:
  - Test ROAD_LENGTH == 70, SPAWN_DIST == 65, EXIT_DIST == 70 consistency
  - Test CAR_COLORS has 15 entries
  - Test RIGHT_TURN_DATA keys match DIRECTIONS keys
  - Test each RIGHT_TURN_DATA entry has required fields (exitDir, cx, cz, a0, a1, r0, r1)
  - Test LANE_OFFSET + INTERSECTION_SIZE/2 == TURN_RADIUS + 2*LANE_OFFSET (geometry sanity)
- Run tests, commit: "Add constants integrity tests"

## 1.2  Vehicle data tests (target: js/vehicles.js)
- Already covered: VEHICLE_TYPES and EMERGENCY_TYPES are in tests.js
- Add:
