# ============================================================
# PHASE 2 — EXTRACT MODULES (one file at a time)
# ============================================================
#
# Order: constants first (no dependencies), then leaf modules, then
# modules that import from earlier ones, then main.js last.
#
# After EVERY extraction: run `node tests.js` + `npx playwright test`.
# If anything fails, fix before moving to the next module.

## Target file structure:
#
#   js/
#     constants.js    — all constants, DIRECTIONS, SIGNAL_STATES, WAVE_DATA, etc.
#     state.js        — mutable game state object (single `state` export)
#     audio.js        — Web Audio: ensureAudio, playSound, playHonk, etc.
#     scene.js        — Three.js setup: initScene, buildIntersection, buildCop, etc.
#     vehicles.js     — VEHICLE_TYPES, createVehicle, updateCars, isCarSignaledToStop
#     pedestrians.js  — createPedestrian, updatePedestrians, ambient peds, bus passengers
#     collisions.js   — checkCollisions, showCrashEffect, showNearMissWarning
#     night.js        — setNightMode, updateCarNightLights
#     weather.js      — initWeather, setWeather, updateWeather
#     difficulty.js   — WAVE_DATA, getWaveData, updateDifficulty, showWaveAnnouncement
#     gestures.js     — initGestureDetection, onGestureResults, updateGestureUI
#     controls.js     — keyboard handlers, cop rotation, camera update
#     main.js         — game loop (animate), startGame, triggerGameOver, init
#   index.html        — HTML + CSS only (~525 lines), <script type="module" src="js/main.js">

## 2.1  Extract js/constants.js
- Move: All `const` declarations from CONSTANTS section (lines 534–580)
          ROAD_WIDTH, ROAD_LENGTH, INTERSECTION_SIZE, CAR_LENGTH, CAR_WIDTH,
          CAR_HEIGHT, STOP_LINE_DIST, CROSSWALK_DIST, SPAWN_DIST, EXIT_DIST,
          LANE_OFFSET, RIGHT_TURN_CHANCE, TURN_RADIUS, NO_TURN_TYPES,
          BUS_STOP_DIST, BUS_STOP_DURATION_MIN/MAX, DIRECTIONS, RIGHT_TURN_DATA,
          SIGNAL_STATES, CAR_COLORS
- Export: All as named exports
- In index.html: Replace the constants block with
    `import { ROAD_WIDTH, ... } from './js/constants.js';`
- Run tests + e2e
- Commit: "Extract js/constants.js"

## 2.2  Extract js/state.js
- Move: All `let` declarations from GAME STATE section (lines 585–648)
- Export: A single mutable `state` object with all properties
- In index.html: `import { state } from './js/state.js';`
  Replace all bare references (e.g., `cars` → `state.cars`, `score` → `state.score`)
- IMPORTANT: This is the biggest mechanical change. Many functions read/write
  these variables.  The `state` object pattern lets modules import + mutate
  without circular deps.
- Run tests + e2e
- Commit: "Extract js/state.js"

## 2.3  Extract js/audio.js
- Move: Lines 651–798 (AUDIO section)
  Functions: ensureAudio, playSound, playWhistle, playHonk, playAngryHonk,
             playCrash, playScore, startSiren, updateSiren, stopSiren
  Data: SOUND_FILES, soundBuffers, MAX_CONCURRENT, activeSources, audioCtx
- Imports: (none from other modules — self-contained)
- Export: All audio functions + preloadSounds
- In index.html: `import { playHonk, playWhistle, ... } from './js/audio.js';`
- Run tests + e2e
- Commit: "Extract js/audio.js"

