# ============================================================
# PHASE 3 — UPDATE TESTS TO USE SHARED CONSTANTS
# ============================================================

## 3.1  Refactor tests.js to import from js/constants.js
- Since tests.js runs in Node (CommonJS), and js/constants.js is ESM:
  Option A: Keep mirrored constants in tests.js (current approach — simplest)
  Option B: Convert tests.js to ESM (rename to tests.mjs or add "type":"module")
  Option C: Create a js/constants.cjs that both can use
- RECOMMENDED: Option A for now (least disruption).  Phase 3 is optional.
  The mirrored constants are a small maintenance cost vs. the risk of
  breaking the test harness.
- If Option B: update package.json, update `node tests.mjs` command
- Run tests + e2e
- Commit: "Refactor tests to share constants (optional)"

